## 1. Vectors

A **vector** is one of the most basic R data structures. R’s intro/manuals center vectors heavily, and data frames are built from equal-length vectors. ([CRAN][2])

```r
favorite_foods <- c("apple", "papaya", "dragonfruit")
print(favorite_foods)
```

Access by index:

```r
print(favorite_foods[1])
print(favorite_foods[3])
```

Important difference:

* Python and TypeScript use 0-based indexing
* **R uses 1-based indexing**

Add an item by creating a new combined vector:

```r
favorite_foods <- c(favorite_foods, "grapes")
print(favorite_foods)
```

### Real-world examples

Web app:

```r
menu_items <- c("Home", "Products", "Cart", "Profile")
```

Automation:

```r
files_to_process <- c("report.csv", "users.csv", "sales.csv")
```

Scientific:

```r
measurements <- c(21.5, 22.1, 21.8)
```

