## Compare the four

### Vector

* ordered
* one main data type
* very central in R

### List

* flexible
* mixed types allowed
* good for one structured record or nested values

### Factor

* categorical values
* important for statistics/data analysis

### Data frame

* table-like
* columns usually built from vectors
* one of the most important R structures

