## Indexing reminder

R uses **1-based indexing**.

```r
colors <- c("red", "blue", "green")
print(colors[1])  # red
print(colors[2])  # blue
print(colors[3])  # green
```

That is one of the biggest differences from Python, TypeScript, Rust, and Go.

